    <Descriptive_Notes>
      <Descriptive_Note>
        <Note_Text>Group of oaks native to North, Central, and South America distinguished by having long, acorns that mature in 18 months, are very bitter, and the inside of the acorn shell is woolly.</Note_Text>
        <Note_Language>English</Note_Language>
